[[Image:Bellville-depot.jpg|thumb|left|300px|The 1890s [[railroad]] depot in Bellville. The town celebrates "Railroad Days" once a year.]]
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of 2010, there were 123 people, 54 households, and 42 families residing in the city. By the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], its population increased to 127.

